id: pm-uzmf
title: "Calendar agent ergonomics: equal start/end rejected; schedule-less Event items invisible"
description: "Dogfood 2026-05-22 (related to pm-fu5d CAL1): (1) start=+Nd,end=+Nd (identical offsets) is rejected as equal start/end - agents naively pass identical offsets; auto-treat equal start/end as an instant event (or interpret bare end as end-of-window). (2) pm create event 'Title' with no --event schedule creates a Type=Event item that never appears on the calendar (no events array) - warn at create time or surface schedule-less events with a 'no time set' note."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 3
tags: []
created_at: "2026-05-22T15:44:35.471Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T17:56:34.741Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: "Implemented and merged calendar event ergonomics: equal start/end becomes an instant event, schedule-less Event creation emits a warning, and duration= derives event end times."
expected_result: Calendar/event commands accept common agent event inputs or give clear guidance without making schedule-less Event items invisible.
actual_result: "Instant events, duration-derived end times, and schedule-less Event warnings were verified in main and the item was closed on 2026-05-23."
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T04:07:36.745Z",calendar-ux-subagent,"calendar-ux-subagent: implemented all three findings (pm-uzmf parts 1+2, plus pm-fu5d CAL1 duration=).\n\nFILES CHANGED:\n- src/cli/commands/event-validation-messages.ts: reworded EVENT_END_AFTER_START_MESSAGE; added new EVENT_END_DURATION_MUTUALLY_EXCLUSIVE_MESSAGE constant (both shared, both imported by create.ts and update.ts).\n- src/cli/commands/create.ts: parseEvents now reads duration= and delegates to new resolveEventEndAt() helper; added schedule-less Event warning.\n- src/cli/commands/update.ts: parseEventEntries now reads duration= and delegates to a parallel resolveEventEndAt() helper (kept consistent with create.ts; did NOT touch the reconcileBlockedByDependency/blocked_by regions).\n- tests/unit/create-command.spec.ts and tests/unit/update-command.spec.ts: updated old equal-start/end rejection tests to instant-event assertions; added new regression tests.\n\nTASK 1 (instant events): endAt < startAt still throws EVENT_END_AFTER_START_MESSAGE. endAt === startAt now collapses to an instant event (end_at dropped, end=undefined), no throw. Applied identically in both parse sites.\n\nTASK 2 (duration=): new field on --event in BOTH parse sites. When duration is given and end is NOT: endAt = resolveIsoOrRelative('+'+normalizedDuration, new Date(startAt), 'event.duration') -- reuses the existing relative-offset parser with startAt as reference. Leading + optional (2h and +2h both work). end + duration together throws EVENT_END_DURATION_MUTUALLY_EXCLUSIVE_MESSAGE. Resulting endAt validated > startAt. UNIT NOTE: the shared relative parser treats m as MONTHS (not minutes); supported units are h/d/w/m -- there is no minutes token, so duration=30m means 30 months. Did NOT modify src/core/shared/time.ts.\n\nTASK 3 (schedule-less Event warning): in create.ts, when resolved type.toLowerCase() === 'event' AND no events attached (events.values undefined or empty), push warning code event_without_schedule:<id>:no_time_set to the create result warnings array. Never blocks. Did NOT touch calendar.ts.\n\nDEFERRED: compound relative durations like +1d+2h (the shared parser explicitly rejects compound expressions; duration= satisfies the finding via single-token offsets). Minutes durations also unavailable (parser limitation; would require touching shared time.ts -- out of scope).\n\nNEW MESSAGES:\nEVENT_END_AFTER_START_MESSAGE = \"--event end must be strictly after start. Equal start/end timestamps are treated as an instant event (end is dropped); an end earlier than start is rejected. Omit end for an instant event or set end later than start.\"\nEVENT_END_DURATION_MUTUALLY_EXCLUSIVE_MESSAGE = \"--event end and duration are mutually exclusive; provide only one (use duration=<relative> like duration=2h, or set an explicit end).\"\n\nTESTS: tsc --noEmit clean. Focused vitest (PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1, create+update specs): 2 files, 96 tests passed. New/updated regression tests cover: instant event from equal start/end (create+update), duration= sets end (create 2h and +1d; update 3h), end+duration mutually exclusive (create+update), end<start still errors (create+update), schedule-less Event create warning + no-warning-when-scheduled.\n\nCOORDINATOR ACTION NEEDED (shared files I did NOT touch): add CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased] entry; optionally document duration= and instant-event behavior in calendar/event docs and SDK contracts if --event sub-fields are enumerated there.\n"
  "2026-05-23T17:07:12.694Z",claude-code-agent,"VERIFICATION 2026-05-23 (coordinator): both findings + CAL1 confirmed in main @398fb079 (PR #45). Dogfooded against freshly-built dist in temp dir: (1) instant event — `create event --event 'start=+1d,end=+1d'` accepted (no error, end dropped); `start=+2d,end=+1d` correctly rejected with the reworded EVENT_END_AFTER_START_MESSAGE explaining equal==instant / earlier==invalid. (2) schedule-less Event — `create event 'NoSched'` (no --event) emits warning `event_without_schedule:<id>:no_time_set` (non-blocking). CAL1 duration= — `create event --event 'start=+1d,duration=2h'` derives end_at = start+2h; end+duration mutually exclusive. Implemented in create.ts/update.ts + event-validation-messages.ts. Closing."
close_reason: Both findings (instant events from equal start/end; schedule-less Event warning) plus CAL1 duration= implemented and merged to main (PR #45 commit 398fb079) and re-verified by dogfooding freshly-built dist in a temp dir on 2026-05-23.
body: ""
